reviewText: It duplicated DVDs I already had by it's deceptive title.  I thought it was videos I didn't have.

These DVD's were great. As usual Chuck Norris was his usual self. I was not disappointed with the condition of the movies. They arrived at my address in great condition. I wouldn't expect anything less when ordering from Amazon or any of Amazons affiliates.

For 13 dollars, You get three very entertaining Chuck Norris movies. If your'e looking for life-changing thrillers try something else, but if you want four and a half hours of engaging Chuck Norris action for a price that's cheaper than a rental, look no further!

1. The President's Man  - Joshua McCord (Chuck Norris) is ready to think about retiring from his grueling job as a Secret Service agent who's assigned to protect the president. As he prepares to train his replacement, however, the First Lady gets kidnapped, and McCord must lead a dangerous mission to retrieve her safely!

2. The President's Man 2: A Line in the Sand - Secret Service agent Joshua McCord (Chuck Norris), after rescuing the First Lady from terrorist kidnappers, returns to protect the country in a special assignment. This time, the president (Robert Urich) needs McCord to chase down and stop a terrorist who plans to detonate a nuclear weapon in the US!

3. Logan's War: Bound by Honor - When Logan Fallon (Eddie Cibrian) was ten, his prosecutor father invoked the rage of organized crime, and Logan's entire family was executed by a hit man, but Logan avoided death with the help of a psychic sense that warned him of impending danger. Knowing the identity of the murderer, Logan decided not to tell investigators, but instead put into motion a long-term plan for revenge!
